# Immediate Tool Code Placement

When the user pastes tool code and asks to add/build it:

- Implement immediately in the repo (do not only explain).
- Use the user-provided code as the primary source of truth for behavior.
- Place code in the expected structure unless the user specifies different paths:
  - `lib/<tool>.ts`
  - `app/api/<tool>/route.ts`
  - `components/<ToolComponent>.tsx` or `app/tools/<tool>/page.tsx`
- Wire route + imports + page so the tool is usable end-to-end.
- Add the tool to the currently active tools category the user is building.
- Update tool slug mappings used by `/tools` (including platform mapping when needed).
- Run a build check after wiring, then commit and push when complete.

Do not stall on extra planning or repeated confirmation once code is provided.
